	<section id="projects" class="section--projects">
		<h1>#  CellMan</h1>
		<p> CellMan is an abbreviation of Cell Management Board, a printed circuit board I designed for Lafayette College's FSAE team as part of our car's Battery Management System. Each CellMan mounts to a prismatic LiFePO cell and measures its voltage and temperature to be reported back to a central Pack Management Board, (PacMan). Each CellMan Board also contains a flyback converter for facilitating an active balancing circuit between the cells.</p>

