		<h1>#  WJRH Website</h1>
		<p>WJRH is Lafayette College's student run radio station. As a member of their engineering team, I've been working to replace their website with a more modern one. It is written using VanillaJS and sports a number of fun features, including a music player and functional spectrum analyzer. The website uses a GraphQL API to query information from the station's various backend resources, such as music metadata and program schedules.</p>

